  <steps>
    <step order="1">Confirm Wave 1 task 023 shipped `<SendEmailPage />` exported from `@spaarke/ui-components/src/index.ts`. If not exported, raise blocker (do not proceed).</step>
    <step order="2">Read the wrapper's prop API (`ISendEmailPageProps`) from Wave 1 task 023's output file.</step>
    <step order="3">Update `package.json` — add `@spaarke/ui-components` as a workspace-local dep (or matching version pattern to DocumentRelationshipViewer if it uses the same).</step>
    <step order="4">Update `src/App.tsx`:
      - Import `<SendEmailPage />` from `@spaarke/ui-components`
      - Consume `authenticatedFetch` from auth context
      - Consume parsed URL params from task 032's `useUrlParams()` hook
      - Map URL `id` → `communicationId`, `to` → `initialTo`, `cc` → `initialCc`, `subject` → `initialSubject`, `body` → `initialBody`, `associatedTo` → `associations` (array or singular per wrapper API)
      - Render `<SendEmailPage authenticatedFetch={...} mode={...} communicationId={...} initial...={...} onSent={...} onClose={...} />`
    </step>
    <step order="5">Implement `onSent` and `onClose` callbacks:
      - `onSent`: log telemetry; if launched from Form Component Control, call `Xrm.Page.ui.close()` if available; otherwise route to a success state
      - `onClose`: similar — close form or navigate back
    </step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm run build`; confirm clean build; resolve any TypeScript prop-mismatch errors.</step>
    <step order="7">Grep verification: confirm `@spaarke/auth` is NOT imported anywhere in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/`. Document grep output in task notes.</step>
    <step order="8">Local smoke: serve the Code Page locally (npm dev or equivalent), open with `?data=...` for each of the 5 modes, confirm `<SendEmailPage />` renders for each mode and shows the appropriate UI (empty for compose; loaded record for view).</step>
    <step order="9">Wait — this is a FULL-rigor task; insert checkpoint after step 9 if context > 60%.</step>
    <step order="9.5">QUALITY GATE — Run `code-review` on `src/App.tsx` + the mount integration; run `adr-check` against ADR-026 + ADR-028 + NFR-02. Confirm: (a) wrapper consumed correctly; (b) auth boundary upheld; (c) no Critical findings.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 033 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed; advance to next pending task (034).</step>
  </steps>

